Demonstrate `StackOverflowError` by finding the max safe recursion depth:

```java
static int depth = 0;
static void recurse() { depth++; recurse(); }
try { recurse(); } catch (StackOverflowError e) { /* depth is max */ }
```

Implement `findStackLimit()` returning the approximate max depth.

**Key insight:** Each frame takes ~100-200 bytes. Default stack is 512KB-1MB. Typical limit: 5000-20000 frames.

